      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is GBP automation?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">GBP automation means a tool automatically creates, optimizes, and publishes content to your Google Business Profile without manual input. This includes posts, review responses, profile optimization, and directory submissions. True automation means you set it up once and it runs on its own — versus "management" tools that make manual work faster but still require your involvement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How often should I post to Google Business Profile?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Weekly minimum. Businesses posting 4+ times per week consistently rank higher in the local pack than those posting sporadically. theStacc publishes 30 GBP posts per month — roughly daily — and Merchynt's Paige maintains a regular automated schedule. Google rewards profiles that demonstrate active management.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I automate Google review responses?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Merchynt's Paige and Birdeye both offer AI-driven review responses that publish automatically. Paige handles this fully autonomously, including negative review responses in an appropriate, brand-safe tone. Local Falcon's Falcon Agent feature also includes auto-reply capabilities, though it's still early-stage. theStacc doesn't currently auto-respond to reviews.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is GBP automation allowed by Google?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google's Terms of Service allow third-party tools to manage GBP profiles via the Google Business Profile API. Tools like BrightLocal, Merchynt, and Yext are officially recognized partners. Automated posting, optimization, and review management are all compliant, provided the content is relevant and not misleading.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Which GBP automation tool is cheapest?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Localo's free plan is the cheapest entry point. theStacc at $49/month is the cheapest option for post automation specifically — 30 posts per month, fully automated. Moz Local at $20/month is the cheapest for directory distribution. For full autonomous GBP management including reviews and citations, Merchynt at $99/month covers everything in one tool.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do GBP listings revert if I cancel my tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">It depends on the tool. Yext's listings revert to their previous state when you cancel — your information is removed from directories. Whitespark's manually-built citations persist permanently because they're submitted directly, not maintained via API. Posts you've already published to GBP through any tool remain on your profile regardless of cancellation. Always check the cancellation policy before committing.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can one tool handle GBP + blog content + social media?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is the only service on this list that automates all three: 30 GBP posts/month, 30 blog articles/month, and 30 social media posts/month. Every other tool focuses on GBP-only or includes GBP as a module within a broader SEO platform. If you want unified local content across all channels, the Stacc bundle at ~$126/month is the only option that doesn't require multiple subscriptions.</div>
